# ComputerJobs CTO Process

## Before ANY task

1. Read `.cto/RULEBOOK.md` (index)
2. Read relevant specialized files in `.cto/`:
   - ARCHITECTURE_RULES, DATABASE_RULES, PRISMA_RULES, NEXTJS_RULES
   - AI_RULES, SECURITY_RULES, SEO_RULES, DEPLOYMENT_RULES
   - CODE_STYLE, REVIEW_CHECKLIST
3. Check `docs/adr/` and `docs/DECISIONS.md` for prior decisions
4. Rulebook wins over conflicting instructions

## Code structure (mandatory)

- `src/modules/{feature}/` — all business logic
- `src/modules/shared/` — env, logger, prisma, redis, queue, storage only
- **Never** add new code to `src/lib/`
- AI: `src/modules/ai/{gateway,providers,...}/`
- Taxonomy & location: use mandated subfolders

## Git workflow

- `main` — production
- `develop` — integration
- `feature/*` — e.g. `feature/auth`
- Conventional Commits

## Phase completion

Generate `docs/phase-{N}/CTO_REPORT.md` + `docs/reviews/ARCHITECTURE_GUARDIAN.md`

## Phase 1 name

**Identity & Access Management (IAM)** — not auth-only
